-- Finmeccanica to Give Pansa More of CEO’s Powers, Repubblica Says
-- B y   A n d r e w   D a v i s
-- 2012-05-16T07:16:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/finmeccanica-to-give-pansa-more-of-ceo-s-powers-repubblica-says.html
Finmeccanica SpA (FNC) ’s board plans to
transfer some powers from Chairman and Chief Executive Officer
Giuseppe Orsi to Chief Operating Officer Alessandro Pansa,
newspaper la Repubblica reported, without saying where it got
the information.  Pansa will take responsibility for acquisitions and
strategy, while Orsi, who is the target of a bribery probe,
remains in control of personnel and external relations, the
newspaper said.  The board will transfer the powers after a shareholder
meeting today to approve a record 2.3 billion-euro ($2.9
billion) loss for last year, Repubblica said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Davis in Rome at 
